Situation: A few months from now your app is growing and you get a new data format
from your places API. Instead of semicolons it now uses a pipe | as a separator:

"Mo-Fr 09:00-17:00 | Sa-Su 10:00-15:00"


You go into parseOpeningHours and update the segmentRegex to handle the new format.
While fixing it you accidentally break the existing comma separator logic.


That's the core value — tests act as a safety net when you change existing code.